{
  "texts": [
    "For the loss curves, see Appendix D. Projection Update Period T: We first analyze the influence of the projection update period T on the convergence of of LLaMA-130M when trained with CompAct.To do so, we conduct experiments with varying update intervals.",
    "A learning rate of 5e -3 is used by default, but if training becomes unstable at a given T, we reduce the learning rate until stability is achieved.",
    "As shown in Figure 5, an optimal T range emerges: updating the projection matrix too frequently or too infrequently both slow down convergence.",
    "This trend remains consistent across the couple of ranks we show.",
    "Steps: Next, we investigate the effect of rank and training duration on model convergence.Here, LLaMA-130M is trained with a projection update period of T = 200 and an initial learning rate of 5e -3, which is reduced to 4e -3 if instability occurs."
  ]
}